and good at Frisbee.

133
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:38,009
His point is that your brain is
really good at doing some

134
00:05:38,009 --> 00:05:39,170
tasks that your computer
and your

135
00:05:39,170 --> 00:05:40,860
smartphone can't do well--

136
00:05:40,860 --> 00:05:44,000
at face recognition, at
complicated ballistics

137
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,170
problems like running around
and catching a ball.

138
00:05:46,170 --> 00:05:48,650
But it's not very good at
remembering phone numbers.

139
00:05:48,649 --> 00:05:51,289
Those kinds of tasks are better
done by a computer.

140
00:05:51,290 --> 00:05:53,700
The way that evolution has
shaped our brain has given it

141
00:05:53,699 --> 00:05:57,099
a distinct set of skills, and
these are shaped by our

142
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:59,050
evolutionary needs.

143
00:05:59,050 --> 00:06:02,340
Consciousness, logic,
complex thought--

144
00:06:02,339 --> 00:06:04,619
these are all evolutionary
latecomers.

145
00:06:04,620 --> 00:06:08,629
They are built upon and added
on top of a much older and

146
00:06:08,629 --> 00:06:10,930
earlier set of brain
functions--

147
00:06:10,930 --> 00:06:13,120
ones that we use every day.

148
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:15,639
We've learned about our
brain's talents and

149
00:06:15,639 --> 00:06:17,969
limitations, in part from the
study of robotics and

150
00:06:17,970 --> 00:06:19,690
artificial intelligence.

151
00:06:19,689 --> 00:06:22,860
It was surprisingly easy to
build computers that were

152
00:06:22,860 --> 00:06:25,129
better at certain tasks
than we are--

153
00:06:25,129 --> 00:06:28,250
for example, at remembering
the phone book, or even at

154
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:31,040
beating the greatest chess
champion in the world.

155
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:34,129
However, it's been much more
difficult to get robots or

156
00:06:34,129 --> 00:06:37,569
computers to do things like
to play soccer or

157
00:06:37,569 --> 00:06:39,159
recognise your kids.

158
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:42,490
In fact, those tasks are
really difficult.

159
00:06:42,490 --> 00:06:46,160
We're misled by how easily we do
them, because that's really

160
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:49,110
what our brains have
evolved to do.

